{"cursor":"7323","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox film | name = Frozen| image = Frozen 2007 film.jpg| caption = |\ndirector = Shivajee Chandrabhushan| producer = Shivajee Chandrabhushan| writer =\nShanker Raman (screenplay) Shivajee Chandrabhushan (story)| starring =\nDanny Denzongpa Gauri Rajendranath Zutshi Aamir Bashir| music = John P.\nVarkey | cinematography = Shanker Raman | editing = Shan Mohammed | distributor\n= | released = | runtime = 109 minutes| country = India| language =\nHindi Ladakhi | budget = | }} 'Frozen' is a 2007 black-and-white Indian drama\nfilm directed by Shivajee Chandrabhushan. The original screenplay written by\nShanker Raman, based on a story by Chandrabhushan and starring Danny Denzongpa,\nGauri, and Skalzang Angchuk. The film was shot entirely on location at Ladakh,\nIndia. [http://www.booksie.com/editorial_and_opinion/book_review/lubusait/f-\nrozen-warm-ladakhi-fare FROZEN Warm Ladakhi Fare Film review] [http:/-\n/www.hollywoodreporter.com/hr/awards_festivals/fest_reviews/article_display.jsp-\n?&rid=9865 Festival Review - Toronto International Film Festival] Hollywood\nReporter, 19 September 2007.\n\nIt was featured at the various international film festivals, including the 2007\nLondon Film Festival and Dubai International Film Festival, [http://www.altfg.com/blog/film-festivals/frozen-at-the-dubai-film-\nfestival/ Dubai Film Festival 2007: FROZEN] and was the official selection\nat 2007 Toronto International Film Festival and 2008 San Francisco International\nFilm Festival, and Palm Springs International Film\nFestival. [http://efilmcritic.com/review.php?movie=16473 Frozen 2007] efilmcritic.com. [http://www.dubaifilmfest.com/en/movies/a-\ncelebration-of-indian-cinema/frozen.html India/2007/Hindi, Ladakhi dialogue with\nEnglish subtitles/B&W/35mm/110 mins] Dubai International Film Festival [http://www.psfilmfest.org/festival/film/detail.aspx?id=196-\n92&fid=35 Frozen, 110 mnts.] Palm Springs International